Readability	✅ More readable for large objects	❌ Slightly more code for manual instantiation
Immutability	✅ Immutable by default	❌ Mutable (setters allow changes)
Required Code	✅ Less boilerplate	❌ More boilerplate
Performance	⚡ Same as traditional approach	⚡ Same as @Builder

📌 When Should You Avoid @Builder?
	•	When working with JPA/Hibernate Entities (@Builder can cause issues with lazy loading).
	•	When you prefer explicit constructors for clarity.
	•	When creating very simple objects with only a few fields.

